==College career==
While attending [[Louisiana State University]], Edwards played for coach [[Les Miles]]' [[LSU Tigers football]] team from 2009 to 2012. He finished his college career with a total of 96 tackles, 10.5 sacks, two interceptions and two forced fumbles.<ref>{{cite web | title= Lavar Edwards LSU  Statistics | work= sports-reference.com/ | url=http://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/players/lavar-edwards-1.html |accessdate=}}</ref>  On January 25, 2013, he was selected to participate in the [[2013 Senior Bowl]].<ref>{{cite web | title= Russell Shepard, Lavar Edwards Set for Senior Bowl | work= sportsnola.com | url=http://www.sportsnola.com/sports/lsu/592010-russell-shepard-lavar-edwards-set-for-senior-bowl.html |accessdate=25 January 2013 }}</ref>

